values:
nearly two months in, i know that i know more than i did when i started this job, but if there isn't something about working in a field of Very Smart People [tm] that makes me feel so incredibly stupid.

fear is the mindkiller.

the hardest part of not having an exciting social life is being unsure what (if anything) is the right thing to put on various social networks.

also, doom.

now that i've made the mistake of tying each of my online identities to who i really am in real life, it's hard to remember where i've decided it's okay to confess things about my real life concerns.

such as they are, anyway.

all of the cool kids are updating this week.

i probably should be reflective about life soon, anyway.
[this is a placeholder post, because i fully hope to post before labor day]

to talk about my flaws today

i'm not entirely sure how to do that.

eight days (or possibly, i guess, more)

new goal: upgrade my collection of stories to include things that have happened within the last five years of my life.  emphasis on the past year of my life.  this may require doing thing that are worthy of sharing as stories.

[not that my life is poor, but i could always use more.]

every time i go to a bar event with a keynote speaker who's admired by hundreds of colleagues, i feel a little sad.

when they die, kings will come to their funerals.

i need to find a way to live that will allow friends to come to mine.  but also kings.  because dead people love crowns, you know.

it is my intention to run through a self inventory at the end of this week.

it really feels like today is tuesday, and like this week is never going to end.

standard space ghetto disclaimer - DO NOT CLICK ON LINKS THAT SAY "SPACE_GHETTO" WHILE IN POLITE COMPANY

That said, http://www.spaceghetto.st/sgd/index.php?q=node/32604 is my new dream party.  For, like, ever.

on thursday, my father informed me that when i was in undergrad, he wished i would become a rapper or a professor instead of an engineer.

he also wished i had been a rapper or professor instead of a lawyer.

how the fuck does one end up with that set of possibilities?  "well, here at the university of michigan, where your best hasn't been good enough since 1817, we offer such majors as underwater basketweaving, being a trust fund kid, at least five top ten ranked engineering degrees, business degrees, and rapping, which features a minor in becoming a professor."

i hate everything.

also, in case you didn't see on facebook, if you find me my next job, i will give you $500.  seriously.  preference is for intellectual property law, in house counsel, engineering, or an NPO, but i'm technically flexible.  bsme and j.d., for whatever that's worth.

as time goes on, it seems apparent that i know less and less compared to what i used to know.  

i think i peaked at 9.  i was perfect in fourth grade.  pretty sure of it.

now i don't have to actually talk to that ex girlfriend from nine years ago to know that she's not married.  i am kind of curious what happened about her master's degree, though.

[yes, i could have just used twitter for this]

welcome to my life
free drinks and bad advice

[it's not much but my money's on you]

i gave kids (all of whom were older than i was) advice about how to find jobs they might be interested in.  i don't know if that makes me a hypocrite, liar, or just unsuccessful at using the techniques i described.

when i get text messages, i read them outloud half the time, usually in a character voice having nothing to do with the person sending it.

I'm sometimes afraid to post crap to twitter for fear some stupid robot will add me based on something i type.

i really need to get motivated to be a better man.

i sometimes wonder how people can handle not spilling their emotional guts to the internet to avoid from keeping everything inside (and toxic).

then i realized that most people are able to talk about their feelings with real people relatively often.  in the past four years, i don't think i've truly spilled my guts to a person.

i really should get a therapist, maybe.  but not this guy: http://thepeoplestherapist.com/

i am in desperate need of another couple of shelves. like, two more. also, a longer wall.

i can't tell if this is the quarter life crisis, ordinary stress, career/job worries, or a need to have artistic talents that i don't actually have, but i sort of want one of those stupid tumblr things.  or art skills.
maybe you should get a tattoo that says "warning" that's all, just a warning.

apparently, this list is definitive: http://www.rottentomatoes.com/guides/worst_of_the_worst/1/

i've seen the following:

babylon a.d.

i'm actually really surprised i haven't seen more of the things on this list.  and that films like "dungeons & dragons" and "antitrust" failed to make this list.
it's much harder to be completely unproductive without reliable wireless.  similarly, harder to use lj as more than an rss feed when nobody is posting things here.

after a conversation with my favorite jewish 1/3, i really like the idea of moving to dc commune.

on the other hand, i am apparently serious about grown up relationships, and am mostly comfortable being in michigan (as long as i am occasionally allowed to leave on weekends).  this is a conundrum.

also, there is no government work in the state.  there are probably engineer jobs, but who knows how to get those?

also2, i hate when the people i need to talk to are partners and leave before four pm so they can play golf.  

also3, mixtapes for girls are ready.  artwork for mixtapes for girls is not.
must remember that i can upgrade my phone this month.  must decide if that's a good idea.

in short, i'm probably feeling so out of sorts and imperfect because i have a psuedo-urban life, but no urban tribe.

how do you fix that?

At night my thoughts run to the morning. Even in my dreams I feel like I'm playing catch up.

And yet in quiet nights, like tonight, I realize much nicer some of my life could be if I weren't always trying to get to the next end point, multitasking. I watched a movie today. Just the movie. No books, no laptop, no texts. It felt odd.

I don think things are supposed to feel like that.

On a related note, I feel like I should be interesting enough to write about myself wiki style. I don't know why I don't, except that it would be boring.

Facebook tells me that two more exes are married. My other ex tells me I'm a commitmentphobe. This upsets me.

I love, you laugh.

Phizzle out

and now you know what it looks like when i try to blush. also, this week is crawling.

New life goal: do things on occasion that distract me from how much of my life revolves around my job. 

Related goal for monday: MC Frontalot in Ace Duece this week (today). Gogogo. 

Also, yesterday was the first time in a while that I realized how odd my relationships with my exes might be. 

Make no mistake, he puts the "man" in manipulate. 

Phizzle out

current status: unhinged uncertain about my future unsingle so pretty much the same as always. you're excited, because it's halfway like content. there's a chance that i need to find a way to talk to someone more often. i don't know how i feel about my inability to be self counseled. also, i'm in need of mangoes. phizzle out
if you ever sleep over and want breakfast at my place, remember that i take very unflattering pictures and think nothing is sacred.
[i really do have things to say, but i also have a lot of work left to do this weekend, and only 12 hours before i need to be in the office.]

war games 2: the dead code
scorpion king 2: rise of the warrior
beastmaster
doom

are are typically as well communicated.

actually, i'm a phenomenal sharer of thoughts, all the time.  it's my thing, really, which you no doubt are already aware of.

1. i was thinking today about the fact that it takes a special effort for me to share what's going on in my life. since i don't really see anyone everyday, the elements of my daily existence that make it to my friends and lovers have to rise to some threshold level of importance.  particularly with people who aren't able to guess my mood from my tone of voice, this sometimes creates problems when i share details after they are no longer presently important. 

2. i read something yesterday about the difficulty of finding someone intelligent who wants to work hard.  [no observations about it, i just want to remember that i read it.]

3. i was reminded (as ever) that my friends are great and talented in areas i never can/will be.  i obviously know this subconsciously, and also am obviously unsure how to avoid the need to compete with everyone about everything.  it seems obvious that i should accept that i'm probably decent at something since i know so many talented people.

facebook is clearly still relevant among my friends, but based on the automatic lists it sets up, it's apparent that many of my friends and lovers have graduated from the need for constant, stalker friendly narcissism.

livejournal, are you the same?

et tu, twitter?



if a recluse posts in the woods, is it more than just electrons?

[no content today]

as people keep graduating (which, it seems, they are wont to do) i have to wonder, who's going to provide my internet with content?  also, when everyone stops using the internet to talk about their lives, will i get more or less productive?

i, unwisely, always believe that one day life is going to start to untangle itself. i don't need or want anything huge, not all at once. but if i could tell whether or not i had any hope of being a good practitioner, i wouldn't complain. i thought at 25 i'd have made a few grown up decisions. i also worry that i spend too much time alone. i don't know what to do with that much solitude. but i also don't know how to prevent myself from becoming too involved with the people i do hang out with. cutting myself off from others on occasion is essential, but sometimes i can't help thinking i have too many things to entertain myself when i'm alone. i have a job where meetings are discouraged and frankly, i don't see any of the people who are my age regularly. my friends increasingly are far away, but tend to come together relatively frequently. i tend to live vicariously through that, laughing and smiling at the inside jokes that i'm still part of. but i do it at home, hundreds of miles away from them. [and sometimes, realizing that laughing out loud by yourself makes you seem crazy, i skip that too.] this weekend, aside from hockey, i don't think i said any words outloud. some days, i realize that aside from walking into the office and saying hi to the receptionist (and doing the same when i leave) i don't say anything. i'm sometimes startled by the sound of my own voice. i'm pretty sure that's an imperfect experience to have. at the same time, if i truly believe my job is important (i do) and i don't want to have a roommate (i don't) and i'm not ready to get married/live with someone/adopt a kid for the tax break or vacation. i don't know what that leaves me with. i do know that something is missing. let me know if you find it.
